main event: An observer in Green Lake, Wisconsin, reported seeing a solid object with sharply outlined edges that descended into clouds and then disappeared from view on April 27, 1967.
interesting points: The object was described as bright white, shading to white-blue on the bottom,The sighting lasted for 15 minutes and was recorded during cloudy weather with a cloud density of 300',The object appeared solid and was compared in size to a match head at arm's length,No photographs of the sighting are available, The observer also reported the object made a steady sound similar to a small gas engine.
sighted object: a bright and solid aerial object
